docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:61:| A-057 | A rejected Credit Manager review extends the §24.4 request with top-level `rejection_reason_category`, `detailed_reason`, `reapply_allowed_flag`, and `communication_mode`; `rejection_stage` is fixed by the workflow to `credit_assessment`. These extra fields are required only for `decision = rejected`, while `reviewed` and `returned` continue to accept exactly `decision` and `review_comments`. | M04-FR-011 requires the review action to generate the existing rejection note, but §24.4 names only decision/comments while §21.3 and data-model §13.6 require category, detailed reason, reapply flag, and communication mode. Requiring the source fields avoids inventing defaults; fixing the stage is an invariant of the appraisal workflow rather than caller choice. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M04-FR-011; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §21.3/§24.4; `docs/source/data-model.md` §13.6; `docs/slices/006F2-credit-manager-appraisal-rejection.md` | 006F2 and later rejection/sanction slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If source governance defines a nested request or different review fields, version the adapter while retaining the public appraisal/rejection-note module seams and existing stored note contract. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:66:| A-062 | Witness list/create uses `GET/POST /api/v1/loan-applications/{id}/witnesses/` with narrow `members.witness.read/create` permissions. Compliance Team Member and Company Secretary receive both; Credit Manager and Internal Auditor receive read only. A qualifying witness must match a member name, have verified member KYC, and hold at least one active shareholding with positive shares. | Source schema and S09 make witnesses application-scoped; the permission naming convention and stage matrix state the actions/roles, but the permission catalogue and endpoint map omit exact codes/path, and the sources do not define how persisted shareholding status/count qualifies a shareholder. The nested path and conservative active-positive test are standard defaults that prevent caller-forged verification. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S09; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §11, §12.2, §15.4, §26.4, §34; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §7.2 | 004E-witness-shareholder-validation and future documentation workflow slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance adds canonical witness permission codes, endpoint shape, name-matching rules, or shareholder qualification, version the adapter and seed while preserving application scope and persisted verification evidence. |
