docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:69:| A-065 | Verified PAN/Aadhaar corrections use `POST /api/v1/members/{id}/reverification/` with current `version`, at least one identity value, and a reason. The action atomically resets member KYC to pending; the last member creator/editor cannot verify the resulting member KYC document. | M02-FR-012 requires an approved change request and the slice requires a reverification path, but API §13 names no approval-case resource or endpoint. A dedicated reasoned transition avoids silently overloading PATCH; maker-checker is enforced at the existing KYC verification boundary without inventing an approval authority. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M02-FR-012; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §13; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §18/§25.1; `docs/slices/006Y-member-create-update-and-identity-governance.md` | 006Y and future governance confirmation | High | Yes | 2026-07-12 | If governance defines a formal identity-change approval case or separate reverification permission, version this endpoint and preserve masked history/audit, optimistic locking, and verifier separation. |
