The first concrete gaps are now evidence-backed. The member backend advertises a reverification action only for verified KYC, yet the write endpoint accepts the same transition while KYC is already pending; it also permits duplicate PAN/Aadhaar despite the cited M02 acceptance rule. Separately, 006X2’s required backend parity matrix is represented by one new eligibility denial test, while the slice names every credit mutation and all authority/state/concurrency dimensions. I’m checking whether these warrant separate corrective slices and auditing the UI/browser evidence before writing findings.
